Name: breast ductal adenoma
Definition: A breast adenoma that is characterized by a prominent fibrotic capsule and a bilayered tubular component.
Synonym: cystic hypersecretory duct carcinoma of the breast

Name: pregnancy adenoma
Definition: A breast adenoma that occurs during pregnancy.

Name: breast apocrine adenoma
Definition: A breast adenoma that is characterized by apocine differentiation.
